<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How do I calculate the length of my shift?", answer: "Enter your shift start time and end time. The calculator subtracts the start from the end to give you total shift hours and minutes. If you have a break, enter the break duration in minutes and the calculator will show both total shift time and paid (net) time after the break is deducted." },
  { question: "Does the calculator handle overnight shifts?", answer: "Yes. If your end time is earlier than your start time (for example, starting at 10 PM and ending at 6 AM), the calculator automatically detects an overnight shift and calculates the correct duration by adding 24 hours to the end time before subtracting." },
  { question: "What is the difference between total hours and paid hours?", answer: "Total hours is the full duration from start to end. Paid hours is the total minus any unpaid break time. For example, an 8-hour shift with a 30-minute unpaid lunch results in 8 total hours but 7.5 paid hours. Paid breaks would not reduce this number." },
  { question: "Can I enter break time in minutes?", answer: "Yes, enter your total break time in minutes. Common values include 15 (short rest break), 30 (standard lunch), 45, or 60 minutes. The calculator subtracts this from the total shift time to calculate your paid hours." },
  { question: "How accurate is the shift duration for payroll?", answer: "The calculator provides exact time calculations based on the times you enter. For payroll purposes, verify that the times match your actual clock-in and clock-out records. Some employers round to the nearest quarter hour, which this calculator does not do. Always confirm with your payroll department for official calculations." }
]) %>

<%= calculator_schema(
  name: "Shift Duration Calculator",
